
/*
 * This Hyperlambda code sends a signal through a socket to a specified feedback channel. It constructs a message using the concatenation of strings and sends it with a type of "info" to the subscribers of the feedback channel. The [sockets.signal] slot is used to broadcast the message, and the [args] node contains the message details. The feedback channel is dynamically determined from the [.arguments] node. 
 * 
 * 1. [sockets.signal] - Sends a signal to the specified feedback channel.
 * 2. [args] - Contains the message details to be sent.
 * 3. [message] - Constructs the message content using string concatenation.
 * 4. [type] - Specifies the type of message as "info".
 */
sockets.signal:x:@.arguments/*/feedback-channel
   args
      message:x:@strings.concat
      type:info
